<h1>Administrative And Professional Experience</h1>
<ol start="1" type="i">
<li>Director of Studies, National Institute for Policy and Strategic Studies  (NIPSS), Kuru, Jos (Jan. 2015 – Jan. 2019).</li>
<li>Directing Staff and Sabbatical Fellow, National Defence College, Abuja (2007-2008).</li>
<li>Commissioner for Education, Cross River State, Nigeria (2003-2007).</li>
<li>Consultant, ECOWAS Commission, Abuja (Early Warning System and Security Harmonization, 2013-).</li>
<li>Member, University of Calabar Governing Council, 2009 to 2013.</li>
<li>Chairman, Governing Council, The Polytechnic, Calabar (1994-1998).</li>
<li> Visiting Professor and Head of Department of Political Science, Delta State University, Abraka (1998-2000).</li>

<li>Head, Department of Political Science, University of Calabar        (1989-1990; 2001-2003).</li>

<li>Sub-Dean, Faculty of Social Sciences, University of Calabar (1997-1998).</li>
<li>External Examiner/Assessor (Professorial Positions): University of Nigeria, Nsuka; Obafemi Awolowo University, Ile-Ife; Abia State University; Nigerian Institute of International Affairs; Nnamdi Azikiwe University; University of Uyo; University of Port Harcourt; University of Benin; Niger Delta University, Bayelsa State; University of Sokoto; Delta State University; University of Ibadan; Benue State University.</li>

<li> Member, Faculty of Social Sciences Editorial Board and Conferences/Seminar Coordination (1986-1990</li>

<li>Member, Panel of Investigation into the Organization and Conduct of NUGA ’90, University of Calabar.</li>

<li>JAMB Examiner (Government), (1986-1994).</li>
<li>Facilitator, National Population Commission (1991 Census).</li>
<li>Guest Lecturer and Examiner, National Defence College (1992-2013).</li>
<li>Guest Lecturer, National Institute for Policy and Strategic Studies, NIPSS, (1993-2013</li>

<li>Senior Research Fellow, Nigerian Institute of Internal Affairs, Lagos (1992-1994).</li>
<li>State Coordinator of Training and Research, Centre for Democratic Studies, Abuja (1989-1994).</li>

<li>Member, NUC Accreditation Panel: Abia State, OAU, OOU, Covenant, UNIBEN, Igbenedion, Osun State, Afe Babalola, Joseph Babalola, Salim Universities. (1996 - 2014);Odumegu Ojukwu University, Akwa, 2016</li>
<li> Federal Government of Nigeria Technical Adviser to the Independent Electoral Commission of Liberia in 1997.</li>

<li>Vice-President, Social Science Academy of Nigeria (1999-2003).</li>
<li>Vision 2020 Committee on Foreign Policy (April to July, 2009).</li>
<li>Guest Lecturer and Examiner, Institute for Security Studies, Abuja.</li>
